<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4875&amp;p=43612#p43612"><![CDATA[
Sur a disassembly is great for ROM hacking, but it doesn't need to be <em>complete.</em><br />Only the part that are to be ROM hacked, which are usually close to the I/O stuff and far away from the core engine, are worth disassembling.<br /><br />If you want a complete ROM hack that changes 100% of the ROM then you might as well write a new game.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Mon Feb 23, 2009 10:47 am</p><hr />
