<title type="html"><![CDATA[Starting a Comprehensive Disassembly of SMB3]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4875&amp;p=43603#p43603"><![CDATA[
I got some ideas from the RE docs of SMB, even though I don't code for NES.  For starters, my GBA game had a collision test loop that ran every object.  Even with sorting, it killed performance.  Then I decided to structure the object routines more like SMB and only tested collision when an object had to move (it takes place in a large scrolling room with lots of stuff, think SMB2/Doki Doki with 30 mushroom blocks in one room).  Also, jump tables!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3506">strat</a> — Sun Feb 22, 2009 8:36 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
